h3.p:
Pedigree breeding starts with the crossing of two genotypes, each of which have one or more desirable characters lacked by the other. If the two original parents do not provide all of the desired characters, a third parent can be included by crossing it to one of the hybrid progeny of the first generation (F

 1

). In the pedigree method superior types are selected in successive generations, and a record is maintained of parent–progeny relationships.
